review_blob: 12 oz can. Clear pale yellow pour with zero head or lacing. High carbonation. Good apple pie flavor yet a very watery champagne mouthfeel. 6.9 ABV is undetectable. Good, but not NEARLY as good as Sprechers Hard Apple Pie.
beer_name: Cigar City Cider and Mead Homemade Apple Pie Cider

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Clear maroon-pink pour with no head or lacing. Taste is sweet but tart with a hint of dark cherry flavor. Dry finish. Wine-like. 6.9 ABV is well hidden.

Clear dark cherry cola pour with a beige head that vanishes instantly. No lacing. As expected, it smells and tastes just like a cherry soda. Sweet with high carbonation. Very refreshing but not really beer. 5.5 ABV is well hidden.
Dark brown pour with a tiny fizzy beige head and zero retention or lacing. Strong root beer nose and flavor. Drinks and tastes like a soda. Refreshing, but not really beer.
12 oz can. Brewed in DeBary, FL. Semi clear amber pour with a khaki head and good retention. Spotty lacing. Floral nose. Hoppy taste but with a soft bitterness. Not my favorite style but not bad.

This is not as good as last years version. Clear mahogany pour with a thick beige head and decent retention. Fair lacing. Dark fruit and malty taste, but more bitter than before. 7.7% ABV is very evident and a little harsh.
The 2014 was more of a true brown ale. This is now a harsh winter warmer. Bring back the 2014 version!
Semi clear dark copper pour with a tiny head and no retention. No lacing. Weird taste for an Oktoberfest. Like a smokey Scottish ale. Not terrible but this is no Oktoberfest.
Simply the best. Liquid nostalgia. Clear pale yellow pour with a white head and decent retention. Very good lacing. Clean, crisp, sweet light lager taste. Super refreshing.

Clear gold pour witha large off white head and good retention. Good lacing. Taste is a good mix of American and German Oktoberfest beers. Great lager taste with lighter malt and caramel flavors. 6.0 ABV is well hidden.
Draft sampler at Craft Brews in the Park in Viera. Cloudy medium amber color with a huge off-white head. Taste is an excellent mix of vanilla and brown ale with some cinnamon notes.
Clear light amber color with a light khaki head and average retention. Good lacing. Pretty light caramel taste for an amber but a very good smooth pale lager. Very sessionable.
Clear mahogany pour with a thick khaki head and excellent retention. Good lacing. The taste is less spicy than a typical pumpkin ale, and thats good. Kinda tastes like a smokey amber ale.
beer_name: Florida Beer Gourd Shorts Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Clear bronze color with large thick off white head and excellent retention. Spotty lacing. Sweet and smooth caramel flavor. Very enjoyable.
Cloudy light orange-yellow color with a big off white head that didnt last long. No lacing. Good pumpkin spice taste. A little on the wheaty side. Enjoyable.
Cloudy straw yellow color with a white head and limited retention. Spotty lacing. Lager taste is a little paler than BMC. Decent but wouldnt seek it out.

Tasted as part of a flite. Very dark red color. Good lacing. 10.3 ABV is very evident and masks any flavors at all. No cranberry or spice taste evident. They call this a strong ale. TOO strong. Alcohol burn.
beer_name: Barley Mow Gryla Cranberry Spiced Ale

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Clear dark amber color with a foamy tan head with good retention. Looks and smells great. Decent lacing. Nice pumpkin flavor without over spicing. Nice. Just cant have a lot of them.
beer_name: Magic Hat Wilhelm Scream Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Clear golden color with a fluffy white head and good retention. No lacing. Sweet and smooth/mellow but bittering hops. Not my favorite style.

12 ounce bottle. Nice brown ale flavor with a little seasonal spice added. High alcohol content but you wouldnt know it by the taste (unlike many others). Many people here will hate it simply because its from AB but its pretty good.
I was hoping for better. Should be categorized as an amber pale ale. Still too hoppy for my palate. Candy sweetness? I think not.
Just a plain pale lager.  Nothing outstanding but didnt taste bad either.  Just a fresh light-tasting beer.  Smooth.  The kind of beer that drives the craft beer snobs crazy.
WTF, are you people all nuts?  This beer is monkey piss.  Skunky and sour.  It is the only beer Ive ever bought and had to send back as undrinkable.  Disgusting.
